&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.2;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Legend Biotech is a global biotechnology company dedicated to treating, and one day curing, life-threatening diseases. Headquartered in Somerset, New Jersey, we are developing advanced cell therapies across a diverse array of technology platforms, including autologous and allogenic chimeric antigen receptor T-cell, T-cell receptor (TCR-T), and natural killer (NK) cell-based immunotherapy. From our three R&amp;amp;D sites around the world, we apply these innovative technologies to pursue the discovery of safe, efficacious and cutting-edge therapeutics for patients worldwide.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.2;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.2;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Legend Biotech entered into a global collaboration agreement with Janssen, one of the pharmaceutical companies of Johnson &amp;amp; Johnson, to jointly develop and commercialize ciltacabtagene autolecuel (cilta-cel). Our strategic partnership is designed to combine the strengths and expertise of both companies to advance the promise of an immunotherapy in the treatment of multiple myeloma.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.2;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Legend Biotech is seeking &lt;strong&gt;Administrative Assistant (Contractor) &lt;/strong&gt;as part of the &lt;strong&gt;Admin&lt;/strong&gt; team based onsite in &lt;strong&gt;Raritan, NJ.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Administrative Assistant is to support Legend’s CAR-T Manufacturing site at Raritan, NJ. The Administrative Assistant will provide a variety of administrative support and will be involved in and help coordinate special projects and executive initiatives on behalf of Plant Leadership. The successful incumbent will be self-motivated, have excellent interpersonal skills and the ability to build professional relationships. Individuals must have the ability to work independently and also as an effective and engaged team member. Strong initiative and follow through is essential for this position. The ability to maintain confidentiality and to operate in the role with the highest of ethical standards and professionalism are required.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be responsible for all forms of communications to ensure clear communication across the team and with key stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide executive administrative support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain plant organizational chart and headcount files.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists with compilation of data from various sources, organize the data in formats to facilitate analysis and presentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support HR on plant-related recruitment and onboarding activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and drive completion of key deliverables, proactively following up on outstanding items, such as compliance trainings, vaccination records, and as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in the planning, coordination, and preparation of project plans, plant communications, dashboards etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties may assigned as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mi

